[SN]TITLE[SN]
Hawick house fire death not suspicious

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Police have said the death of a woman in a house fire in the Borders is not being treated as suspicious.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Kelly Falconer, 45, originally from Surrey, was discovered in the property in the town's Fisher Avenue on 13 April after fire crews arrived at the scene.
Police Scotland initially said the death was being treated as unexplained.
A joint investigation with the Scottish Fire and Rescue Service has now concluded there were no suspicious circumstances.
